content.detailedDescription:
Sighting report:   i know this sounds crazy but you have to
 belive me.  at 6:10 pacific time, i observed a unidentifed
 craft, in what s still daylight, fly over almadan vally in san
 jose.  it had four lights, positioned like on the tips of a
 dimonand, 2 of them which were blinking several colors.  it
 slowly crused across the sky, making a "looooooooo" sound as it
 zoomed away from me.  i wasn t drinking or anything!  please
 help me make sense of this! 
  
 - scott hamelton

Sighting report:   i was outside taking bodie my dog for a walk
 when i saw pretty much a ufo. it was hovering about 75-150 feet
 above me. it had 4 bright lights. 2 of which were blinking
 different colors. it made a whoaaaaaawlllllllll sound. not too
 loud, but i could hear it. it hovered there for a bit, something
 like 25 seconds, then zoomed off northeast. i was outside for
 about an hour now waiting to catch something then i decided to
 report it. thank you.

Sighting report:   at about 8:45 i saw something in the sky i don t know if it was a ufo or a plane or whatever but it had 4 lights 2 white 2 blinking different colors, it stoped for a second in the sky then sped off faster then anything i ve ever seen

Sighting report:   dowell first of all i have recently heard,that
 around 90%of ufo sighting describes so-cold ball of light,i have
 seen this phenomena two times ,frankly speaking i do not feel
 like describing it all over again for a couple of reason:the
 most important is,i do not see the point way you guys demand ,or
 wait for reports about it,and at the same time the public in
 general do not receive any explanation ,what the hell this 
 glowing balls  are?The other irritating thing is when so cold
 expert try s to estimate the reliability of the person who
 encountered it,i have got the impression that the only reliable
 people to make a report are police-haha ,i wouldn t trust polish
 police.

Sighting report:   i was sittng in my flat listning to the
 radio(without the lights on & facing the window) when i noticed
 a shimmering light in the sky. at first i thought it was
 nothing, but it was still there after 10-15 minutes so i had a
 more detailed look and i could see there was a seies of colored
 lightblue. red, blue red coming from the object. i haven t got a
 pair of binoculars, so i got my camera and put on the telescopic
 lense for a better view, what i saw was: this object with theses
 colored lights. it seemed to change:(this is difficult to
 explain) the lights continued to flash, but changed color to a
 yellowish/golden and at the same time the object seemed to
 change shape, ut i could not distinguish the shape, it just
 changed. once the lights changed to (six i think)in two rows of
 three. the object did not appear to move, but the position did -
 i suppose it was the earth moving - as it remained in this
 relative position to my flat for the 2+ hours that i watched it.
 when i first noticed it i phoned my friend who lives approx.
 half a mile away and she saw it too. she rang me back approx. 1
 hour later to say it was still there. what was it?

Sighting report:
>i just took these photos with my digital camera and was wondering if they can be analized? they were taken from my house in los angeles on dec 18th 2004 at around 11:30-40am.  the object was moving extremely slow, almost not moving or hovering. there are aircraft that fly in the same general area but it was moving extremely slow and there were no contrails. also, it is obvious when it is an aircraft as i have seen them flying in the same area.The object looked very high in the sky and it dont think it was a baloon or anything. im just wondering if someone can check it out. im kind of curious as to what it was. attached are the photos
content.summary: Slow moving hovering ufo captured on film

content.detailedDescription:
Sighting report:   oh my fucking god i just saw a fucking ufo
 outside. i was giving my dog her food and i hear this sound. it
 wasn t a loud sound more like a soft sound, it sounded like
 "loooooo". i look up and there s these lights i can see through
 the clouds. it s cloudy right now i could only see the lights, 2
 lights were white facing opposite to eachother, other 2 lights
 were going in a circle around themselves and were red and
 greeen, there were another 2 lighs that were also swirling
 around themselves and were facing opposite to the other 2, and
 they were also red and green. it was like a square made of
 lights but you could only see the corners. i was so shocked when
 i saw it i just started up and didn t move until it wasn t
 visible anymore. it just disappeared into the clouds, it s very
 cloudy right now which is rare here in phoenix arizona. i came
 to my senses when my dog jumped on me and then i came inside to
 report this.
content.summary: Square made of 6 lights in the sky

content.detailedDescription:
Sighting report:   hi;
is is sunday night about 8:40 pm i just came in and got the
 computer to send this off to you.  i wasn t sure who to give
 this info to.  if there is someone else i shoudl contact please
 let me know.

i took my binos out to look at jupiter in order to show it oto my
 grandkids.  i took the binos cause i wasn t sure we could get a
 good enough look and didn t want to take the scope out until i
 was sure.  while i was looking at jupiter a "point of llight"
 shot across the planet and kept going.  we live near the airport
 and i thought it was probably a plane but it was much too high
 and much too  fast!  i followed it in the binos.  it went left
 turnied and went right then when straight up and to the left
 again.  no plane or helicopter could have made this manuever.  i
 come form a long line of pilots and know no plane of copter coud
 do this.
sorry i can t describe it better.  anyother reports of anything
 in this area?
thanks
lynn

Sighting report:   april 2, 2005, camp hill, pennsylvania,
 10:15-10:45 pm. clear skies (belt of orion and big dipper
 visible), planes flying also visible.  looked up and saw the sky
 was very clear and traced the belt of orion and big dipper (the
 only stars i recognize).  observed bright blue-red colored
 glowing object in sky close to belt of orion in the western edge
 of sky across from street.  i watched it for several minutes.  i
 then went into my house and asked my roommate to come look at
 the skies as they were so clear.  we went out and looked.  i saw
 the object was still there.  we went back in and got binoculars
 (not real powerful).  we focused on the object and it was
 glowing and changing colors and appeared to quickly jump.  i
 went to 211 south 19th street (my dad s house) and asked him to
 come look.  we took turns looking through binocular.  ed went
 into my house (213) to get a camcorder to record it.  the
 battery was dead so we hooked up electric and brought it out. 
 the object was still there.  dad realized the "jumps" were our
 binoculars moving but we realized the objects were stationary
 and glowing multiple colors.  ed began to film and i noted the
 time and location on the tape as the clock was not on est.  ed
 filmed the object.  i then noticed two other lesser, but
 glowing, similar objects.  i asked ed and my dad to look.  they
 saw the objects also.  there were planes flying and other flying
 lights (planes farther away) so we knew these were not planes. 
 we filmed them all for about five minutes.  we quit and i came
 in to file this report.  we are not alien searchers nor wackos
 looking for ufos.  you are welcome to view the film.  i think
 they are low earth orbiting satellites (although i must confess
 i don t know what they d look like in the sky but that seems the
 most logical explanation) but decied to send this to you anyway.
  thanks!

Sighting report:   last week i was reviewing some photos i had taken
a few weeks ago, on april 18th. i noticed a large speck in the sky
on one shot. using a computer to enlarge the area by 1000% i can see
it appears to have a flat bottom and top of different
circumferences.  the left side of the narrower upper section appears
to either be reflecting or emmitting light. the object does not
appear on the next photo, which was taken less than two minutes
later.
i was facing southeast from the north bank of the schkulkill river,
near the art museum.  the building is across the river.  i didn t
notice the object when i took the photo or when first reviewing
them. there are no other similar objects on any other photos.

Sighting report:   at aproximatly 9:15 at night on april 7 2005. we seen a blue light very silent it moved in a circular motion  it went down then half circle then back up and went straight up and dissapered it was partly cloudy out

Sighting report:   ufo spotting 12:45 am may first, portland oregon:

i live in what is known as the pearl district of portland, a kind of
wanna be hi-so area full of expensive apartments, lofts, gallery
spaces, restaurant etc. right in front of my apartment building is a
park where there s almost always somebody walking their dog. coming
home from work just now i noticed a well dressed man with his dog in
the park staring up into the sky with an expression of wonder and
concern, turning and looking at me he said "there s three strange
lights up in the sky" and when i stopped and looked sure enough
right where he pointed there they were. three dim but definite
reddish lights, two were right above each other, the third above the
two and off to the upper right. they resembled stars in their size
and over the course of several minutes the upper two would fade and
dim out, then reappear at intervals, independent of each other.
finally they faded for good with the upper right one moving off to
the west in the process, the other one just did a stationary fade
leaving the bottom light which then faded in and out as well then
vanished. they seemed to be a high altitude but as i had no way of
establishing scale it s impossible to tell. the gentleman expresses
his gratitude at my stopping and telling him what i was seeing as it
mirrored his own perceptions and relieved him as he was concerned
that he was "seeing things". he also told me that he had been
watching them for about 5 minutes before i appeared and they had
seemed both lower and brighter.
content.summary: Three reddish lights hovering in a trianglar configuration

content.detailedDescription:
Sighting report:   i was sitting on my porch at around 8:35 today
 (march 19) looking at the stars when i noticed something in the
 sky.  it didn t look like an aircraft.  it had several lights on
 it, changing to different colours.  as i stared at it wondering
 what it was i noticed that it was really quiet around me.  about
 two minutes into my observation, the silence was broken by some
 sort of wierd humming sound, followed by a higher pitched "loo"
 sound.  it stayed there for what seemed like an hour, and then
 left.  when i went to tell my wife, she said i had only been out
 for about four minutes.  i m really disturbed by this and i am
 wondering what exactly this was.

Sighting report:   it looked like there were four small, circular
 objects in the sky, all changing different colours (colours
 included blue, yellow, orange and pink or purple, not sure). i
 was outside practicing baskbetball and when i saw it, i told my
 mom to come out and see it, but when she got there, they were
 gone. i thought it was nothing until my friend, jarred, called
 and was completely freaking out and he said he d seen it too.
 jarred reads books about ufos all the time and said that these
 were like something out of the books so i googled a ufo
 reporting site and you know the rest. the crafts seemed to make
 a sound that i could only hear outside of the house, too. it was
 very low pitched and almost sounded like "loooo".

Sighting report:   12;50 pm i was driving south on hwy 183 from
davidson ok, when i noticed a silver ball floating in the sky  the
ball then changed its color into a yelowish biege color that got
very bright in midday,  my brother jeff who was in the passenger
seat was able to see it maneuvering by reappearing from three
different directions evasivly then fading in and out . it would get
bright then fade out and reappear  .No clouds all blue skies. it was
then we noticed jets flying from different directions toward the ufo
it then dissappeared .   the jets military were crisscrossing their
contrails as though they were lost searching . the object apparently
was several thousand feet up. but looked like it was several
hundred.  this was near the red river northeast of vernon texas.  a
woman in a car had pulled over and i believe she was filming this
but i didnt stop .  as i was still trying to get closer to the ufo.

Sighting report:   thursday, june 16, i was out in a field behind my
house. there were only a few clouds in the sky and alot of "stars"
to be seen. after about five minutes of sky watching, i realized
that there were too many stars that appeared to be moving.  i
thought that it was only generalized to a few "stars", but after
looking further, i realized what appeared to be @30 some stars that
were moving.  i thought they could be planes as i am on the  flight
pattern of toledo airport, but there were also lights that
definitely were planes.  as i watched the star lights, they would
stop, reverse and speed forward.  i more i looked back across the
sky, the more moving "stars" i saw.  i was very freaky.  i went
inside. i am going back tonight if there are no clouds.

Sighting report:   i`m not sure of the year it was after `95 i`m
positive because my daughter was born but we have ...What looks
like 2 ufo`s ...For lack of a better word..."fighting" & nobody
will listen or watch it & tell us what it is!!! help!!!!!!

Sighting report:   i saw a dark colored craft in the sky,
 eliptical in shape. it had 4 lights that were mostly solid but
 blinked a bit. it flew overhead and into the distance heading
 east. it seemed to make a droning noise as it went, like
  loooooo . not normal. neighborhood dogs were barking.

Sighting report:   i was getting ready to retire from my job as a
 professional firefighter and was in the process of moving to a
 small town 60 miles north, nahunta georgia, to get out of the
 big city. i still had 3 months to work and had to drive to
 jacksonville fl. every third day to work.The first leg of the
 trip was from nahunta to folkston ga. a 30 mile strip of nothing
 but pine trees, bur half way was a small crossroad and 6 or 7
 houses in a small town called winokour. on the morming of june
 4th or 5 or 6th 1995 5:30 am  ( i am not shur of the date ,but
 it was the day that a hurricane was coming ashore at cedar key
 fl. ).
 but being a firefighter i had to go to work regardless. just as
 i passed winokour (a few thousand feet) i saw a row of lights at
 the top of the trees on the right. at first i thought, they bult
 a factory here,and then then i thought it couln t be, i was here
 yeasterday and there was nothing there. then i thought ,i m on
 the wrong road,then i thought ,i cant bei just passed the small
 town of winokour. then realiazing this was somthing else i
 slowed down to a stop.I couln t see it through the right window
 and had to lean forward to look up and to the right at the top
 of the trees and sitting there at tree top height was this
 gigantic thing, sitting there motionless and silent, with all
 the lights on. i oped my door to my truck and stepped out with
 my left foot and stood up and looked over the top of my truck at
 this craft. at this point i was only 60 feet away from it. it
 spanned the distance of 3 telephone  polls. the night was pure
 black and no moon . i could hardly see the shap of it because it
 was so big.And i was almost directly under it.  but there was
 what seemed to be a row of lights . from the ground they seemed
 to be about 3ft wide and 4 ft high. and about  8 ft. between
 them.And maybee 40 of them.They glowed pale orange and i could
 not see through them. the skin of the craft  was as black as the
 night. this was no blip of light in the night and no metalic
 object at 5000 feet it was right there in front of me and it
 scared the daylights out of me. i did get a thing that kept
 going over and over in my head ( get out of the area) so i did
 and went to work.
 when i got there and being there was a hurricane coming in and i
 was driving fron so far away they said they didn t expect my to
 come in today and was making arrangements to call someone in to
 work for my ,so i said thats fine with me. knock me off sick and
 i ll go home.Being i had a lot of sick days saved.I returned by
 8:00 am and ther was nothing there, it was daylight and they had
 left. 
do i consider this to be a ufo ,not really, i consider it to be a
 ifo (indentified flying object) and not one of ours. this was
 certanly a real craft. it would be hard for someone to stand
 beside this ,and look at somthing as large as a battleship and
 say , i dont know what i am looking at.

Sighting report:   i was taking out the trash at my friend s
 apartment in woonsocket, rhode island, and i caught a glimpse of
 something moving across the sky. it looked like it was going
 from east to west, or maybe southwest. i can t be sure. all i m
 sure of is that it was going extremely fast, faster than an
 airliner but the size of a cessna or something. it was fairly
 high up, so i had a chance to run inside and grab some
 binoculars. it had two white lights on the sides of the craft,
 and two flashing lights on the top and bottom that blinked
 incessantly. the engine made a low-pitched  looo  sound, and
 when it passed directly overhead i heard a tiny voice in the
 very back of my mind that said  y helo thar.  it was like one of
 those afterthoughts you have, but in a distinctly different
 voice than my own, and it disappeared as soon as the craft went
 past me. it headed west, and when i tried to drag my friend
 outside, it was gone.

Sighting report:   i saw a ufo in california some years ago on the
wesrtern edge of the mojave desert.
it was flying at no higher than 50 feet altitude,wa completely
silent, and gave off no exhaust.
it flew perfectly level, the operator was wearing plastic framed
glasses, a short sleeve shirt, and if i had known him i would have
recognized him.
the craft crossed the road ahead of us going slow enough that it
could not have been developing lift in the normal way of aircraft.
it had a clear dome ala george jetson, no reinforcement evident. the
craft was unlit. the cabin may have been lit or the light from our
headlamps could have been making the pilot visible.
this was just about the time that carter had spilled the beans about
the stealth bomber/fighter.
we later saw that vehicle and realized it was nothing like what we
had seen.
this was not a ground effect craft. the windows of my car were open
and the air was still and i was doing about 30-35 mph.
we passed within 50 feet of the craft and crossed its path on the
ground almost immediately.
folks, antigravity is a fact, i ve seen it, and i have no doubt the
pentagons trillions are the source.
let me know if you have experienced anything similar.
thanks
content.summary: Craft with clear dome 50' off mojave desert floor

content.detailedDescription:
Sighting report:   on wednesday, 18 may 2005 at approximately 2000
hours (8pm) i exited the library on holloman air force base and
noticed a large bright semi-circular spot in the sky.  it appeared
to be approximately 5 times bigger than the largest stars that are
usually present.  the moon was out and to my right when viewing the
object.  no stars were yet visible.  it was still light out.  the
object reflected white light like a star and remained stationary.  
it did not appear to be completely circular.  i entered my vehicle
and drove home (approximately .5 mile away) watching the object the
entire time.  i am familiar with the jets on base and did not see
any of them in flight.  once home i watched the object until about
2010 hours and entered my home.  i exited to view the object some
more around 2020 and observed that the object was gone.  it was
considerably darker now and stars (much smaller) were present.  i
called the usaf security forces police station (of which i am a
member) to report the sighting and they related to me there was a
previous caller that also reported the same.  the sky was clear
before and after the sighting.  i know this is near an air force
base; however i feel this was not a conventional aircraft due to the
stationary nature and its apparent size.
-christopher r. ahumada, ssgt, usaf
49th security forces squadron
patrolman

Sighting report:   earlier tonight i saw a ufo. it was really
 weird. it was making a "looooooo" sort of sound. i saw it for a
 little bit. it had a few lights, but it ducked behind a cloud
 before i could get a good view of it. then it went away. i hope
 this helps.

Sighting report:   on friday april 8, 2005 i was scheduled to meet
    someone in the parking lot of schering-plough pharmaceuticals,
    morris avenue in union, new jersey. i had arrived about 45 minutes
    early so i sat in my truck and listened to a radio talk show. it was
    about 1:30-1:45pm and it was a beautiful mostly clear day with some
    very high lines of white clouds on a mostly blue sky. there was some
    breeze, but i don t recall there being much.
    
    i was facing an unobstructed view of the north easterly sky over the
    top of the schering facility and looking at nothing in particular as
    i listened to the radio, when i noticed a dark "dot" moving/flying
    in a slightly undulating manner in a very open section of the sky.
    it was moving from almost straight ahead of me towards my left.
    because it wasn t flying in a straight line with a purpose as a
    plane or jet would, i thought at first it was a bird flying up
    pretty high. i kept thinking that at any second i would see wings or
    see it do something bird-like. i could not estimate how high it was
    since i had no real point of reference. although there were plenty
    of planes and jets going by at various altitudes, i can only say
    that this was a dark dot by comparison; it appeared to be round and
    about the size of the period at the end of this sentence.
    
    anyway, after observing its gently arcing flight, i noted that it
    suddenly stopped and was standing perfectly still in the sky. i
    think this was due north. i kept watching it, now thinking that
    since i can t see wings and a bird wouldn t hover so long that maybe
    it might be a helicopter. it must have remained perfectly stationary
    for at least 45 seconds to a minute. i kept looking and looking at
    it; i took off my sunglasses, put them back on, looked through my
    open side window, through the windshield and then back through the
open window again, but couldn t see anything else except an unmoving
dark dot. meanwhile, planes and jets continued to move about in the
sky although none appeared to pass close by the dot. at no time did
i ever see any shine or glint of sunlight reflecting back from this
object.

anyway, it finally started to move again and now it is moving back
more or less in the direction it came from, from my left to the
right but it appears to be rising up "higher" before it again stops.
i continue to stare at it, and now it appears that small "pieces"
are "shooting" from the top of the dot (the dot now appears very
slightly elongated but not much larger). when the "pieces" come
"arcing" out of it i can t see them anymore, they disappear and the
sky looks a bit fuzzy around the dot. at the time i am thinking to
myself that maybe it looks fuzzy just because i am staring at it so
intently.

after sitting stationary for what i am estimating to be about 10 to
15 seconds the dot moves in yet another direction (more to the
right, but "down" and more level now) and i am thinking it is also
going "away" from me because it appears even smaller. again, it s
flight is not a straight line like a plane or jet, it is more a
gentle arcing motion. it moves quite a distance across the sky (from
left to right but it s in front of me now rather than to my side)
before i see it start to move "up" and very suddenly it is gone
completely.

i keep looking and looking in the same area thinking that the dot
will reappear and i will see that it is a shiny plane, a helicopter
or even a bird, dragonfly or bumblebee, but i do not see it again.
the entire episode lasted for perhaps 5 minutes and i am still
thinking there is a logical explanation as to what it might have
been.

by the way, i am 51 years old and while i am intrigued to imagine
that there might be ufos from other worlds surveying us, i am not
comfortable enough with what i saw to blab to my friends that i saw
a ufo. i did tell a friend who says he has experienced some unusual
sightings, and he suggested i report what i saw for you to
investigate. i have not included my telephone number because my
husband pooh-poohs talk of such "sightings."

Sighting report:   this is a follow up on a report i made involving the luxor light and objects circling it. i have come to the conclusion it must have been birds. i witnessed similar the following night at 3.00 am .  thank you

Sighting report:   at about 8:45 on march 19, i was driving home
 from eating dinner and i looked up to see four lights arranged
 in a circle.  two of them were blinking between about eight
 different colors, including different shades of blue, red, and
 green, as well as several other colors.  the lights hovered for
 a second, and then started zipping around really quickly.  at
 one point, they were spinning at a pace so fast they seemed to
 blend into a yellow, which then shifted to different colors, i
 assume from the changing of the lights.  the thing then flashed
 away.  the lights never lit up the ground, but i noticed another
 driver near me point up into the sky before we had to drive
 away.  my sister wasn t able to get the camera out of the glove
 compartment, despite my frantic waving and shouting.  part of
 the reason was that she didn t seem able to see it, although she
 was looking right at the thing.

Sighting report:   may 19, 2005, at about 21:00 hours, i saw and
heard at least 5 {five} military aircraft chasing or following an
